<h1>Minimum Requirements</h1>
<p>
    Please ensure that your host provides the following:
</p>
<ul>
    <li>PHP &gt;= 5.2.0</li>
    <li>MySQL 4.1+, or SQLite 3+ with <a href="http://php.net/pdo">PDO</a></li>
</ul>
<p>
    All of these technologies are fairly common today. If your hosting provider doesn't have these, you're probably better off switching whether or not you use Chyrp. You might be able to just e-mail your provider and ask them for it.
</p>

<br />
